      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "hi, all. \nMy question:   \nThere is a `TokenContract`,  `PresaleContract`(`PresaleAddress`), and `userAddress`, wherein  `PresaleContract` is deployed under `TokenContract.tokenId`.  Then, user triggers `PresaleContract.contribute(*)` to transfer **MINA ** to  `PresaleAddress`, as pic1 .\n\nthen error occurs:  (as pic2)\n`Error: Top-level account update can not use or pass on token permissions. Make sure that accountUpdate.body.mayUseToken = AccountUpdate.MayUseToken.No;`\n\nerror point:  https://github.com/TokeniZK/tokenizk-finance/blob/5fed3d2a5169765d60925c8046d3933956ff7cdd/packages/contracts/scripts/deploy-token-presale-local.ts#L297\n\n\n**step to reproduce**:\n1) git clone https://github.com/TokeniZK/tokenizk-finance.git     and  'npm install '\n2) npm run libs:build\n3) npm run npm run deploy-token-presale-local -w @tokenizk/contracts\n\nhere is how I deploy `TokenContract`: https://github.com/TokeniZK/tokenizk-finance/blob/5fed3d2a5169765d60925c8046d3933956ff7cdd/packages/contracts/src/TokeniZkFactory.ts#L260C12-L260C28\n\nhere is how I deploy `PresaleContract`: https://github.com/TokeniZK/tokenizk-finance/blob/5fed3d2a5169765d60925c8046d3933956ff7cdd/packages/contracts/src/TokeniZkBasicToken.ts#L127",
